articles.author: Michael Martina, David Brunnstrom
articles.description: China is providing moorage for a U.S.-sanctioned Russian cargo ship implicated in North Korean arms transfers to Russia, according to satellite images obtained by Reuters, as U.S. concerns grow over Beijing's support for Moscow's war in Ukraine.
articles.title: Exclusive: China harbors ship tied to North Korea-Russia arms transfers, satellite images show

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Taiwan faces a difficult national security situation, with China pressing closer all the time, President-elect Lai Ching-te said on Thursday has he announced the appointments of his new security and diplomacy teams ahead of taking office next month.
articles.title: Taiwan's president-elect appoints new team, says island's security difficult

articles.author: Lucy Papachristou
articles.description: When Antony Rudkovsky was about 15, he began to teach himself how to build virtual private networks (VPNs) to access Internet content unavailable in Russia.
articles.title: Russian programmers play 'cat and mouse' game to outsmart censors

articles.author: Michel Rose
articles.description: French President Emmanuel Macron will outline his vision for Europe as a global power on Thursday in a speech he hopes will have the same impact as a similar address he made seven years ago that prefigured some significant EU policy shifts.
articles.title: Macron aims to cement French influence in EU, lift party fortunes with landmark speech

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: North Macedonian presidential candidate Gordana Siljanovska-Davkova held a big lead over incumbent Stevo Pendarovski with votes counted from 99.03% of polling stations on Thursday, but both were short of the 50% backing needed to win outright.
articles.title: North Macedonia's opposition rightist leads ahead of May 8 presidential poll runoff

articles.author: Simon Lewis
articles.description: U.S. Secretary of State Antony Blinken will meet business leaders in Shanghai on Thursday as ties between Washington and Beijing stabilise, pushing to resolve a raft of issues threatening the newly gained equilibrium between the rivals.
articles.title: Blinken to meet businesses in Shanghai as he kicks off a tough China trip

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Australian police said on Thursday they charged five teenagers with terrorism-related offences in investigations following the stabbing of an Assyrian Christian bishop while he was giving a livestreamed sermon earlier this month.
articles.title: Australian police charge five teenagers in Sydney cleric's stabbing

articles.author: Nidal Al-Mughrabi, Dan Williams
articles.description: Israeli warplanes pounded the northern Gaza strip for a second day on Wednesday in a fierce assault that has shattered weeks of comparative calm, and Israel said it was moving forward with plans for an all-out assault on Rafah in the south.
articles.title: Israel says Rafah assault looms; massive Gaza airstrikes end weeks of relative calm

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Thousands gathered across Australia and New Zealand on Thursday at Anzac Day services to commemorate those who fought and died in major conflicts in the nations' history.
articles.title: Thousands mark Anzac Day in Australia and New Zealand

articles.author: Jeff Mason
articles.description: President Joe Biden will sign a bill into law on Wednesday that provides billions of dollars of new aid to Ukraine for its war with Russia, a bipartisan victory for the president as he seeks re-election and a boost to allies who have looked to Washington to support Kiev.
articles.title: After battle with Republicans, Biden to sign Ukraine aid package
